## Design-intent audit

- **Top → bottom shaft.** Entry y=17500, exit y=1500 — vertical drop of 16000 micro_units across the playable column.
- **Six platforms, mixed shapes.** Three wide solid (2500/1800/2000), one narrow ledge (1200), one one-way ledge (1000) for alternate routing, one wide solid exit pad (2500).
- **Two checkpoints along the natural descent.** Both sit on top of solid platforms (platform 3 and platform 5), partitioning the drop into three ~5500-unit segments — consistent with tier-3 cadence in `fault_lines_03_the_drop`.
- **Four ember pickups totaling 8.** Distributed roughly one-per-section, with the highest-value (3) placed near the one-way ledge as a route-finding incentive.
- **Lethal floor beneath the exit.** A void strip across the whole floor (y < 500) plus a lava strip (2500-wide, y < 800) directly under the exit-pad gap — falling past the exit is lethal, satisfying the design intent.
- **Region flavor.** Side spikes in middle bands match the `fault_lines_03_the_drop` pattern of punishing lateral overshoot during dashes.

